WEBVTT

00:01.301 --> 00:02.495
Four months into med school,

00:02.535 --> 00:04.594
and we were getting
on each other's nerves.

00:04.637 --> 00:06.434
Cole was especially good at it.

00:06.473 --> 00:08.634
Cole, you're wearing my scrubs.

00:08.675 --> 00:10.472
I had to wear the ones
my mom made me.

00:11.678 --> 00:14.943
Babe, you know girl scrubs
make my ass pop.

00:14.981 --> 00:16.744
That is so stupid.

00:16.783 --> 00:18.774
Damn, Mama wants a bite!

00:19.619 --> 00:21.211
You know, Cole,

00:21.254 --> 00:23.620
you could be a little more respectful
of other people.

00:23.656 --> 00:27.456
Fine. Maya, that is a lovely sweater.

00:27.494 --> 00:29.758
It really shows everybody
what you're working with.

00:30.363 --> 00:32.024
There, Luce. You happy?

00:32.098 --> 00:34.066
- Ow! What was that for?
- I don't know.

00:34.100 --> 00:35.397
I assume you did something stupid.

00:35.435 --> 00:36.993
- Did he?
- Yeah.

00:37.037 --> 00:38.402
One more for luck.

00:38.438 --> 00:39.871
All right, fall in, losers.

00:39.906 --> 00:42.534
Today, one of you is gonna get
an amazing learning opportunity.

00:42.609 --> 00:45.169
Trang, I need you to put a new gown
on Mrs. Gainer.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.907
Be careful.
She's off her meds, has four-inch nails,

00:47.947 --> 00:50.040
and is convinced
someone's trying to steal her skin.

00:50.450 --> 00:52.611
Hey, Talking Man Baby, come here.

00:54.187 --> 00:56.781
I am parked
in the 10-minute parking zone.

00:56.823 --> 01:00.054
- You want me to move your car?
- No, I love the space.

01:00.093 --> 01:02.220
What I want you to do is to pull out of

01:02.262 --> 01:05.025
and then back into the space
every 10 minutes.

01:05.065 --> 01:08.398
If you get bored, here's a ball
and a half a deck of cards.

01:08.435 --> 01:09.868
I want that ball.

01:09.903 --> 01:12.201
Trang, get over here right now.

01:12.238 --> 01:13.296
I didn't envy Trang.

01:13.339 --> 01:16.274
At some point, we'd all been caught
between Dr. Mahoney and Dr. Cox,

01:16.309 --> 01:18.777
and it felt like being
in a pinball machine.

01:25.485 --> 01:28.579
And it always ended the same way,
with Dr. Cox winning.

01:28.621 --> 01:32.057
Tiny One, run fast now.

01:37.764 --> 01:39.026
Dr. Kelso?

01:39.065 --> 01:42.557
I told you, you can't be coming up
in here stealing all the gauze.

01:42.602 --> 01:43.967
Are you building a giant gauze ball?

01:44.003 --> 01:45.868
'Cause if you are, I want in.
It's on my bucket list.

01:46.106 --> 01:48.233
Actually, I'm here for a medical reason.

01:48.274 --> 01:49.502
I had a bit of a scare

01:49.542 --> 01:52.943
while I was playing a game
of Scattergories with my niece.

01:52.979 --> 01:54.139
You're still on the clock.

01:54.180 --> 01:56.273
She means the Scattergories clock.

01:56.316 --> 01:58.284
She's very competitive.

01:58.351 --> 02:01.809
Anyway, I got a little bit light-headed,
and so we're gonna run some tests.

02:01.855 --> 02:03.220
I wouldn't worry about it.

02:03.256 --> 02:06.054
A few years back,
I got a little light-headed myself.

02:06.092 --> 02:07.320
Turns out it was...

02:08.627 --> 02:10.960
Well, it was diabetes.
That's a bad example.

02:10.997 --> 02:12.965
You'll be fine. You'll be fine.

02:14.701 --> 02:16.032
What up, Dr. T?

02:16.069 --> 02:19.402
Okay, today, as part
of your practical doctoring class,

02:19.439 --> 02:22.306
we'll be conducting physical exams
on one another for the first time.

02:22.342 --> 02:23.570
Cole.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.178
Put your pants back on.

02:26.713 --> 02:30.774
My bad. I thought this was going
somewhere totally different.

02:30.817 --> 02:34.412
People, I said it day one,
I can't teach you without your pants on.

02:35.054 --> 02:37.420
While doing these exams,
some of you may experience

02:37.457 --> 02:39.584
something we like to call
Med Student Syndrome.

02:40.026 --> 02:41.254
It's a common condition

02:41.294 --> 02:44.593
where med students think they have
the disease they're studying.

02:44.631 --> 02:46.496
All right, what I want you all
to do now, though,

02:46.533 --> 02:49.934
is partner up with the person
next to you and get it cracking.

02:50.003 --> 02:54.269
Getting paired up in med school
was like playing a game of win,

02:54.307 --> 02:56.741
lose, or Frank.

02:56.776 --> 03:00.473
Spoiler alert. My skin's super flaky.

03:00.513 --> 03:03.243
Man, I just got totally Frank'd.

03:03.683 --> 03:06.675
I really appreciate you taking time
to check me out.

03:06.719 --> 03:09.085
I'm gonna take care of you,
but first, as you know,

03:09.122 --> 03:11.420
we got to knock out
one of these patient histories.

03:11.457 --> 03:13.084
And we both know how weird
these can get.

03:13.126 --> 03:15.060
Yes, deeply, deeply weird.

03:15.094 --> 03:16.584
What do you say we just dive right in?

03:16.629 --> 03:19.257
Are you currently taking
any medications?

03:19.299 --> 03:21.529
Have you had sex
with multiple partners?

03:21.568 --> 03:23.058
You exercising regularly?

03:23.102 --> 03:24.729
And have you traveled
outside the United States

03:24.771 --> 03:25.863
in the last couple months?

03:25.905 --> 03:28.169
Yes. Hell, yes.

03:28.208 --> 03:31.837
Yes, I go to the bathroom 10 times
a day, which for me is cardio.

03:31.878 --> 03:33.573
- Natch.
- I recently flew

03:33.613 --> 03:36.912
to Bangkok,
but I didn't actually get off the plane.

03:37.617 --> 03:38.675
Right.

03:39.452 --> 03:42.216
That little stunt you pulled with Trang?
Not cool.

03:42.255 --> 03:43.620
I needed him for real hospital work.

03:43.656 --> 03:45.920
Having him move my car,
I'll have you know,

03:45.959 --> 03:48.484
was hospital work of the highest order.

03:48.561 --> 03:50.358
That's exactly what Trang needed.

03:50.396 --> 03:52.261
Driving back and forth
in the parking lot,

03:52.298 --> 03:55.028
reinforcing every stereotype
of Asian drivers.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.434
Look, you're the one
who put me with the med students,

03:57.470 --> 04:00.030
so don't undermine me.
Who's in charge of them, you or me?

04:00.073 --> 04:02.507
I'm in charge of you,
and by the transitive property,

04:02.542 --> 04:05.033
anybody you're in charge of,
I'm also in charge of.

04:05.078 --> 04:08.013
You see, I'm the boss around here.
I can pretty much do whatever I want.

04:08.047 --> 04:11.107
For instance,
I can use the intercom to whistle.

04:11.150 --> 04:12.947
Any loose change, automatically mine.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.749
And I never have to buy chocolate bars

04:14.787 --> 04:16.652
from any of my colleagues'
awful children

04:16.689 --> 04:18.884
to support their horrible school bands.

04:18.925 --> 04:21.894
I can do whatever I want,
and you just have to stand and nod

04:21.928 --> 04:25.455
like the sweet-mouthed little man-boy,
monkey toy that you truly are.

04:26.799 --> 04:27.823
Mine.

04:27.867 --> 04:28.959
Ugh!

04:29.969 --> 04:31.197
Leave.

04:33.072 --> 04:36.200
Even though Dr. Turk warned us
about Med Student Syndrome,

04:36.242 --> 04:37.709
we couldn't help ourselves.

04:37.744 --> 04:40.872
Dr. Turk, I've got scurvy and rickets.

04:40.913 --> 04:42.744
How did I get all the pirate diseases?

04:42.782 --> 04:46.650
That's a walk in the park
compared to my early-onset dementia.

04:47.453 --> 04:48.715
Where's my phone?

04:48.755 --> 04:51.189
Actually, Cole does have
a weird mole on his chest.

04:51.224 --> 04:55.456
Man, forget that mole. I'm more
worried about the pain in my throat.

04:55.895 --> 04:57.522
The T-Pain.

05:02.502 --> 05:07.496
Listen, guys, calm down. You're all fine.
Everything's good.

05:07.540 --> 05:10.998
That's a bruise, you're just ticklish,
and you, my friend,

05:11.044 --> 05:12.204
you got ink on your tongue.

05:12.245 --> 05:15.737
Stop eating your pens.
Cole, the mole on your chest...

05:16.716 --> 05:19.651
Well, actually, the mole on your chest
is something we need to check out.

05:20.219 --> 05:23.279
So, Cole,

05:23.323 --> 05:26.850
unfortunately, the biopsy shows
that your mole is malignant.

05:26.893 --> 05:28.451
You have melanoma.

05:28.494 --> 05:31.258
Skin cancer? Oh, my God, Cole.

05:35.301 --> 05:36.529
How'd you know
it was gonna be malignant?

05:36.569 --> 05:38.833
I didn't. I was prepared for both ways.

05:40.000 --> 05:46.074
